node.text:
It’s time to kick off #AutismAcceptanceMonth! Traveling through airport security may be scary or overwhelming for some people with autism and other intellectual and developmental disabilities (I/DD). We’re here to help make the experience a little easier. Check out our video for tips on how to best prepare for your next trip!

#wheelsup #Travelgram #travelpro #safetravels #ILoveTSA #travelbug #Instatravels #airportqueue #traveler #tipsfortravelers #aviationworld #travelblogger #autismawareness

node.accessibility_caption: Diamond stone discovered at JFK airport and returned to rightful owner

node.text:
🎶 “Diamonds are forever” 🎶

Our officers at John F. Kennedy International Airport (JFK) worked hard to return a little sparkle to one honeymoon vacationer.

Just imagine… you’re a couple of newlyweds making your way through security on your way to your Guam getaway. You grab a cup of coffee at the airport shop, when suddenly your love begins to cry uncontrollably. You think, “what have I done?” only to discover a diamond is missing from that sparkly engagement ring. Now what?

That’s when our officers stepped up to help. Our JFK team searched high and low to locate the missing bling, promising they’d continue to search for the diamond while the newlyweds boarded their flight. The last thing the couple wanted was to miss their honeymoon as well!

Later that day, one of our officers was returning from their break when, out of the corner of their eye, there’s a brilliant glimmer coming from the checkpoint floor. Upon further inspection they’ve located the missing diamond!

The happy couple landed in Guam with a text message and voicemail from our JFK team. The diamond was given back to them upon their return trip.

Shout out to our JFK team for being true rocks under pressure!

#TSA #TrueStory #Honeymoon #DiamondsAreForever #LostDiamond #TSAForTheWin

@misha – We'd do anything for your safety...but we wouldn't 🎶 do 🎶 that 🎵!

Let’s get to the meat and potatoes here…our officers don’t bake up screening procedures. While they do have a knead at times to ask passengers to undergo additional screening, they will always describe the seasoning and ingredients for that need. You may also request private screening at any time. However, don’t expect a drink, massage or mood lighting to be a part of that process. If we happen to ask if the temperature is okay, it’s only because we wouldn’t want it to be too chilly.

Ketchup on all our pat-down and other procedures through our link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Machine gun bong discovered at BOS

node.text:
Well this decision deserves to be roasted. Last time this person traveled must have been the stoned age. Who in their right mind carries a glass machine gun bong as carry-on?

We get it, it’s glass…but what if we started letting everybody fly high-up in the sky with these items? How would you tell them apart from the real thing? Pack your real and replica weapons in checked bags people (yes even your “tobacco gun bongs”, but leave any real, inert or explosive item at home), this isn’t triggernometry.

While we’re on the topic of smoking gadgets. Let’s hash out the deets on traveling with your high heals. Marijuana remains illegal on the federal level. Not that we are in the business of being Debby duber, but if we find your ganja we don’t BHOgart the stash, it’s reefered to law enforcement.

Still need travel question releaf? Our friends at AskTSA can infuse you with some really dank tips. They give supherb answers to all your travel munchies through Facebook or Twitter. Become their best buds today!

node.text:
Based on true events…what happens when you travel with an abundance of yummy tummy funny lucky gummi bears?

We’re a little jelly over here of not having any of our favorite toothless bears. But stick with us as we go over a little travel advice. You’d be beary relieved to know, whether 2.25lbs or more they are good to go, but chances are we may have to screen them to resolve an alarm.

Side note: If you’ve consumed one too many sugar free gummies before your scheduled flight (you know, the one’s that be moovin’, groovin’, and jammin’ on the insides), then you’ll definitely want to arrive early, especially during this peak summer travel.

Coming off your sugar high and still need travel questions answered. Don’t get sour! Our flavorful team at AskTSA is available every day. Toss a question into their DMs. You’ll always be happy with the answers they pull out of their bag.

#TSA #NationalGummiBearDay #AlbaneseCandy #HariboUSA #SourPatchKids #AskTSA

We need some high-caliber help IG FAM! Give this post a double tap, share and a page save. Help us hammer this message out far and wide. You might just impact your neighbor, friend or spouse.

Queue up our version of a Cash hit:

Guns are everywhere, man. Guns are everywhere, man. Incorrectly packed in a carry-on bag, man. They belong in checked bags, man. Correctly packaged for travel, man. Guns are everywhere.

They’ve been found in: @pdxairport, @fly_bur, @iflyida, @phxskyharbor, @dtwshots, @flyneworleans, @reagan_airport, @flyokc and we could keep this song going.

Please, remember to rifle through your bags for prohibited items, especially firearms. Check all the deep chambers of your bag and eject these items accordingly. The recoil when we find them can lead to heavy fines and even TSA PreCheck® suspension.

To learn more about packing your guns & ammunition, center your mouse crosshairs on our link in bio.

node.text:
Don’t be the gingivitis that crams up the security line. Brush up on these healthy travel tips and stop grinding your teeth over our latest crown of a post (IYKYK).

Liquid explosives still pose a threat. Brace yourselves and molar over this guidance. If you can spill it, spray it, pump it, spread it or smear it (who can say that ten times fast?) the liquid item must be 3.4oz or less. These items must be compacted into a single quart bag per person.

Don’t let oversized liquids become the plaque that gums up your travel plans. Follow our 3-1-1 guidance, it will reduce bag check-ups and speed up the screening process for everyone. If you still wanna try traveling with your full size liquids, consider checking it in.

#TSA #Liquids #311 #TSAGuidance #SingleQuartBag
